  "texts": [
    "What is more important, the rules come with support and confidence values associated with them.",
    "Therefore, a small confidence value for either of the two rules, or consequent values that are far from the black box prediction, are strong indicators that the black box prediction should not be trusted very much.",
    "In the worst case, there will be no rule in support of the black box prediction.",
    "In such a case, the prediction should not be trusted, especially for high-stake decisions (e.g., legal or health-related use cases).",
    "The latter are also the types of use cases that would be classified as high risk according to the AI Act of the European Parliament and the Council of Europe."
  ],
